race.comment: KEEP IT LOKI (4) sharp form reversal when he rounded them up effortlessly from back in the pack for a sound win over 1526m at Lismore. Finds a fairly average C2 and winning apprentice sticks. Goes close. TIETAR (1) tough mare who shouldered the 61.5kg at her third run back when a gritty on-pace winner over this track and trip. Doesn't get the same map favours but sure to be thereabouts again. RAMPANT LION (2) up in trip and grade when a dismal eleventh over 1600m at Eagle Farm  in C3 class. Anticipating sharp improvement at this level. HIGH CLASS ROLLER (6) unsuited first-up over 1250m when a plugging seventh over 1250m at Ballina. Comes to hand quickly and can show rapid improvement over this trip.
